OnePlus has launched its 6T McLaren smartphone, which is available for $699 in the US. The device is based on the OnePlus 6T, but packs 10GB of RAM and features McLaren branding on the chassis. It also packs a Qualcomm 845 processor and 256GB of storage. A feature punted by OnePlus is the phone’s Warp Charge 30 charging, which lets users recharge 50% of their 3,700mAh battery in 20 minutes using a wired charger. A 6.41-inch AMOLED display (2,340 x 1,080), dual rear cameras, Android 8.0, a USB-C port, and LTE-A connectivity also feature on the phone.